<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900614-0018</DOCNO><DOCID>900614-0018.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Armstrong World Industries Inc.:   Thomasville Furniture Unit   To Buy Plant From Ladd</HL><DATE>06/14/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   LADF ACK</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   Thomasville Furniture Industries Inc., a unit of ArmstrongWorld Industries, Inc., said it signed a letter of intent tobuy a furniture manufacturing plant in High Point, N.C., fromLadd Furniture Inc. The amount wasn't disclosed.   The purchase, expected to be completed by late July,includes manufacturing equipment, a 205,000-square-footbuilding and about 22 acres of land, the companies announced.</LP><TEXT>   Thomasville Furniture's President Frederick B. Starr saidhe expects production to begin in 1991. He had no estimate oneventual employment at the site.   Thomasville Furniture, based in Thomasville, N.C., and itsaffiliates operate plants in North Carolina, Virginia,Mississippi and Tennessee.   The proposed purchase is subject to approval byThomasville and Armstrong.</TEXT></DOC>